She is (obviously) crazy talented, crazy beautiful, & from what I've observed it seems like she also has a genuinely kind soul.

That said, I do find it kinda funny that they/she went soo above & beyond "PC" for this vid; 

ie "perfectly balanced diversity" --

•2 black / dark skinned women, 
•2 latina / brown skinned women, 
•2 red/auburn haired light skinned women (perhaps of Eastern European ancestry?)..

All drop dead gorgeous of course (including her blonde self), just thought that was interesting. No intended negativity or judgement, simply an observation. 

In regards to the accusations of her "queerbaiting", 
as an older bi/queer leaning, non conforming cis woman of color myself 
I'm not totally sure I know what that term (queerbaiting) actually means; 
HOWEVER,
to me it looks like she is simply growing & experiencing life, learning to be unabashedly comfortable in her own skin & having fun while doing so. 

I seriously don't understand how people can be mad at her for that.

There are much more important issues to be concerned about at the moment..soo many serious issues which urgently need to be focused on & attended to.

Billie seems to be happy & if so I am truly happy for her & wish her a lifetime full of love, happiness, meaning & fulfilment.
